parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended airbag deployment can cause injuries, distractions, and loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents.
symptoms: often while the vehicle is stationary or moving at low speeds
with no apparent reason or collision. In some cases
the SRS light on the display panel illuminates before the airbag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the direct ignition cassette can cause the vehicle to stall, spit, and stutter, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: often accompanied by difficulty restarting the engine
especially after stalling; the vehicle may shut off and restart on its own; the vehicle may stall on the highway
making it difficult and dangerous to control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The chronic engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when driving on high-speed roads.
symptoms: The engine stalls abruptly without warning
making it difficult to control the vehicle safely.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty convertible top motor can cause the top to become stuck in an open position, obstructing the driver's view and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The convertible top becomes stuck in an open position
